# Example environment for the Unreal Engine MCP harness.
#
# Copy to `.env` and fill in the values for your machine, OR set these directly in
# your environment (the `/onboard` skill sets the first two via `setx` on Windows).
# NOTE: the MCP server backfills unset vars from this repo-root `.env` at startup
# (src/server/src/config.ts), and the key-authoring scripts read it too — but the
# pytest harness and build scripts read only the real environment, so keep the
# engine/project vars exported in your shell as well.
#
# `.env` is gitignored; this template carries NAMES + placeholders only — no secrets.

# ── Engine & project (required for builds / logs) ───────────────────────────────
# Engine install root — the directory containing Engine/. Required by
# editor_build_game_target and the pytest harness (tests/harness/config.py).
UNREAL_ENGINE_ROOT=/path/to/UnrealEngine

# Host UE project root (the dir with your .uproject). Canonical var the launcher
# exports; build/cook tools fall back to this when project_root isn't passed.
UNREAL_PROJECT_ROOT=/path/to/YourProject

# ── MCP server (loopback defaults; leave unset to accept them) ───────────────────
# See SECURITY.md before changing HOSTs — binding off 127.0.0.1 exposes an
# unauthenticated, code-executing surface.
# UNREAL_MCP_HOST=127.0.0.1          # MCP streamable-HTTP listener host
# UNREAL_MCP_PORT=8765               # MCP streamable-HTTP listener port
# UNREAL_BRIDGE_HOST=127.0.0.1       # editor C++ bridge host
# UNREAL_BRIDGE_PORT=55557           # editor C++ bridge port
# UNREAL_MCP_LOG_LEVEL=info          # debug | info | warn | error
# UNREAL_MCP_SURFACE=full            # tool surface: full | compact | code
# UNREAL_MCP_MAX_RESULT_BYTES=       # result-compaction threshold (bytes)
# UNREAL_MCP_ISOLATED=               # set (to any value) in a worktree/isolated
#                                    # checkout to disable Live Coding hot-patch

# ── Test harness (defaults shown; override only if needed) ───────────────────────
# UE_MCP_BRIDGE_HOST=127.0.0.1
# UE_MCP_BRIDGE_PORT=55557
# UE_MCP_BOOT_TIMEOUT=420            # seconds to await editor boot

# ── API keys for optional authoring skills (only if you use them) ────────────────
# OpenAI — used by the /icon skill (image generation) and scripts/openai-key.sh.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...

# Google AI Studio / Gemini — used by the visual-critique skill AND the server's
# video-analysis tools (video_analyze / pie_analyze). The server accepts either
# name; GEMINI_API_KEY wins if both are set.
# GOOGLE_STUDIO_API_KEY=...
# GEMINI_API_KEY=...
